node.text:
a particularly incredible aviation photo shot by National Geographic photographer Robert W. Madden in Guatemala City, 1976.
Intending to photograph the aftermath of a horrific magnitude 7.5 earthquake, Bob had just disembarked from a different aircraft and happened to notice this Cessna attempting to land on the highway.
The pilot was presumably intending to deliver food and medicine to the earthquake victims.
A gust of wind proved to be more than the aircraft or pilot could handle, and they ended up colliding with the small truck on the side of the highway.
The occupants of the truck were able to get away just in time, and amazingly, no injuries resulted from the ensuing crash. 
You can follow Bob Madden at @rwmaddenphotog to enjoy more of his fantastic work. ⠀
